    <bioghist id="aspace_7ebf2cf0dbc90f6182639cc4e284952a">
      <head>Biographical Note</head>
      <p>Veronica Melendez is a visual artist currently based in Washington, D.C. She received her
        MFA from the University of Hartford and BFA from the Corcoran College of Art and Design.
        From illustrations of iconic household products to photographs documenting the diaspora of
        Central Americans within the D.C. metro area, her work is greatly influenced by her Latinx
        upbringing. Melendez is the 2018 recipient of the Duke University Archive of Documentary
        Arts Collection Award for Documentarians of the American South.</p>
    </bioghist>
